Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

COMMENCE FORTHWITH  -  EACH COUNT IS CONSECUTIVE TO EACH OTHER AND CONSECUTIVE TO 14CF406 & 14CF529.

superMiscConds.notes: If probation or extended supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.  This applies to all counts and financial obligations.

Obey all of the rules and regulations of supervising probation agent.  
*  Pay supervision fees.  
Participate in counseling deemed appropriate by agent.  Actively search for employment, be employed or attend an educational institution or vocational training program.  
*  Pay fine of $1000 and court costs including all applicable surcharges.  
*  Submit to a DNA sample (Unless previously provided) and pay surcharge. 
***COURT VACATES ORDER FOR PAYMENT OF 31 DNA SURCHARGES***   *  If unpaid financial obligations remain at discharge or revocation, civil judgment to be entered. 
May not have contact with any minors, co-defendants or any victims who have been and can be identified without permission of the agent.  Not to possess or use a computer. Participate in a mental health evaluation.  No possession of electronic devices capable of accessing the internet.  No possession of devices enabled to record visual images or auditory records.  Register as a sex offender for 15 years after the completion of the sentence.  Participate with Sex Offender treatment.  Participate in the creation of a realistic case plan and any programming related to the associated goals and identified Criminogenic Needs.
